servings: 2
course: main course
time required: 35 minutes
---

Remove the stalk and core from the @red pepper{1} and @yellow pepper{1/2} and cut them into thin slices. Peel and finely dice the @garlic clove{1}, finely chop the @flat leaf parsley{3} and cut the @cherry tomatoes{1/2} in half. Chop the @chestnut mushrooms{1} into chunks and boil @water{600%ml} with the @vegetable stock pot{1}.

Heat a tbsp of @olive oil{1%tbsp} on high heat in a #non-stick frying pan{} and fry off the mushrooms. They'll release water, so keep cooking them until this has evaporated and they are dry and browned off (it should take about ~{5%minutes}). Remove them and keep to the side.

Add 2 tsp of @olive oil{2%tsp} into the #frying pan{} and (still on high heat) fry off all the pepper slices and cherry tomatoes for a few mins. Once they have softened up, add in the diced garlic, @rosemary{1%tsp} leaves, the @smoked paprika{1/2} and @ground turmeric{1/2}.

After ~{3%minutes} more, add in half the parsley and the @basmati rice{1}. Cook everything for a few mins until the rice absorbs the oil in the pan.

Next, add the 600ml of vegetable stock and the mushrooms. Give everything a good stir, reduce the heat to medium-low and cook for ~{15-20%minutes}, or until the rice has soaked up all of the liquid.

> Tip: Don't stir the rice, as a good paella always has a crusty bottom!

Have a siesta.

Once the liquid has soaked up, take the paella off the heat and cover it with a clean #tea towel{} for ~{5%minutes}. Season with @salt{pinch} and a few grinds of @black pepper{few grinds} to taste. Serve with the remaining parsley and big wedges of @lemon{1/2}. Ándale!